How to list products on WhatNew

WhatNew Support June 12, 2025 at 12:58 AM

{/* ===== Seller Product Creation Section ===== */}

Product Creation on WhatNew

Product Creation on WhatNew is the foundation of how your products are discovered by buyers. Whether you’re running auctions, flash sales, or Buy It Nows, adding your products ahead of time helps streamline your workflow, keep your show organized, and create a smoother experience for your buyers.

When listing a product, there are two key decisions:

1. Buy Formats

  • Auction: Set a starting price and let buyers bid live (usually ~30 seconds).
  • Buy-It-Now: Fixed-price items available anytime during the show or in your profile shop.

2. Sales Channels

  • Live Show: Your WhatNew live show, where everything happens in real time.
  • Profile Shop: Your store in your profile. Buyers can visit and purchase anytime.

Listing Products From Web

  1. Visit Seller Hub: https://seller.whatnew.com
  2. Click “+” in the top right corner and select “List an Item.”
  3. Add product media by uploading or scanning the QR code to your phone.
  4. Fill in details: Quantity, Pricing, Buy Format, and Shipping info.
  5. Click Publish or Save Draft.

Listing Products From Mobile App

  1. Open the WhatNew mobile app (iOS/Android).
  2. Tap Seller Hub → Create a Product.
  3. Add media, details, and pricing (Buy It Now or Auction).
  4. Tap Publish to go live immediately.

From a Live Show

  • Tap the Store icon → “+” → Choose Listing Type.
  • Temporary Listing: Quick setup for the show, expires when show ends.
  • Quality Listing: Full details, discoverable, helps earn Premier Shop.

Drafts

You can save listings as drafts to finish later. Once published, active listings can be deactivated and reactivated but not reverted to draft.
